caption: Went into So fresh today and purchased a classic bowl. Which normally is called a classic wrap. I asked for the gulf shrimp as well as the herb chicken which is always delicious every time. Especially more so now since it’s what I crave for during my pregnancy. Today was disappointing because I checked my food only to see the portion size was way less then what I normally see and get.  So I asked the girl at the counter did the portion size change. She then laughed and said I got a wrap size portion. I replied and said well I asked for a bowl so she goes to the back and tells the guy to add more lettuce. If I would have paid in cash I would of definitely asked for my money back it was completely rude and very unprofessional.
Quick, healthy food!
Food was okay. Extremely overpriced unless you are okay with no meat, sides, or drinks.
Good food
One of my fav spots for Health food. definitely one of the best places in the area.

Very disappointing. Use to be my favorite spot. Somehow they missed the memo about Covid as I watched an employee from another nearby pizza joint, walk in, NO MASK, to pick up a to go order. Then proceeded to walk behind the counter into the kitchen to talk to the cooks with NO MASK, over the food. They didn't seem to mind. And one of their own continued to walk casually through the restaurant with mask under his mouth. Not sure it's safe to eat here during the pandemic. 😳
Fine location for quality Health food. Food is similar to a place in San Francisco I liked.

I wassss just introduced to this place and I was PLEASANTLY SURPRISED.....IT WAS SOOOO FRESH AND REFRESHING TO TASTE SOMETHING DIFFERENT AND I REALLY ENJOY THE FRESH AVACADOS AND MEAT... CAN'T WAIT TO TAKE MY HUSBAND.
Nice staff, great food, quantity can be little more, but all in all good place for healthy food.
Great food really enjoyed it 😋

Delicious! The warm bowl which consists of whatever you want (build your own), I went with rice and their herb chicken; was well cooked and very well seasoned. I thoroughly enjoyed every bite. Will be trying other items when I am in the office, which is right next door.
Great healthy options for lunch downtown. Gluten and dairy free eating is easy here.
One of my fav spots for Health food. definitely one of the best places in the area. the service was very welcoming and observant. the place has a good feel to it.

SoFresh was meh, to say the least. The restaurant was practically empty as we happened to stop in in the evening. The restaurant was relatively clean, but the tables weren't 100% clean. Our food was made faster than expected, but when they ”completed” our order, they forgot to make our shakes.  My husband wasn't impressed, but I thought the food was decent enough. It basically tastes like an ”end of day” order. I used to work in fast food, and it tasted like there wasn't ”love” put into the cooking — rather, ”I hope this is the last order of the night.” I was still very hungry after eating the entire warm bowl, but I could've just been that hungry.
Mid
Great place to eat if you have gluten and soy allergies. Delicious too!
I dont like kale, but their kale banana smoothie was pretty good.
Fine place for delicious health food. visited at eight, it was not full. the staff was friendly and observant. the bill was good for what you get. this place has positive reviews for a reason.
A top scene for tasty health food. Service is typically good. Mood here reminds me of San Diego's scene.
Really fresh and tasty food here!!!
health food and the scene here is better than most. The place has a great feel to it.
Food is pretty good, but way overpriced for some chopped up vegetables and everything EVERYTHING is an upcharge.
Health food, yummy. Food was so tasty. Nothing but great experiences here. Food is like a restaurant in Jacksonville I liked.

The girl who took my order was extremely helpful, im from out of town and had no clue where to start. But the food Is awesome! They did miss part of my order but she was honest and quick to fix it. Would definitely recommend.
Very good! Did a design your own warm bowl. It was very clean.

My wife and I ate here before our visit to Tampa Hospital down the street.  The service was quick and good.  The options to eat healthy were abundant.  The food was a very large quantity for a moderate price.  The food was really fresh and very tasty.  Thank you SoFresh for the wonderful service.
Second time I went and still great food! So many great vegetarian options!
Love this place, so happy to have one near work. So many options and so far,they are all good!
Tons of healthy food options and the ability to customize. Everything I've had has been flavorful.
Tasty food.
Very good food, loved the green tea with agave.  A little bit pricey, but definitely delicious.  I had the teryaki bowl with dark meat chicken and I would definitely return for another round.
Food was okay but a bit pricy for the quality. There was a hair in my chicken.

I had thought of going to Whole Foods for a quick sandwich but stopped in this new place across the street. Glad I did! Great "bowl foods" with many options. I had the Greek with rice, cucumber, fresh spinach, feta and tzaziki. Just what I needed without that heavy bread. Of course I didn't need the gluten free chocolate chip cookie, but it too was good. Great food! We had a delicious dinner here - warm grain bowls and they were excellent! There was SO much food in these, too! Service was fast and accurate.
Service is amazing and food is top notch!
Price gouging during a pandemic

The broth bowl is everything. It's warm, filling and satisfying😍 Zucchini noodles, carrots, corn in a veggie broth with your choice of protein. I got the herb chicken. It's a must try! High five so fresh ! Delicious!
Each time it gets better! Really helpful staff too.

My boyfriend and I went to this place last weekend. We ordered the same thing as each other (power bowl with chicken, and mine had extra cheese). When the cashier totaled out the price, I noticed he charged us for double the amount of chicken. I brought it to his attention, and he removed the double chicken on each bowl, leaving only one order of chicken on each bowl, which was correct. My order also said extra cheese as it was supposed to. We live almost an hour away, so when we got home and went to eat (trusting that the  orders were correct) they were most definitely not correct. His didn't have chicken AT ALL, and mine had no cheese. You'd think after I corrected the cashier twice, the order would be correct. Aside from the awful communication skills of the staff, the food was good.
Good food, but a little bit expensive if you choose steak (way more than Fresh Kitchen for example)
Check wait time before ordering if busy! I had to wait 40 minutes for a single salad (to go) on Saturday 2/15/2020. Order placed 2:36 PM, order received 3:16 PM 🤬.
My go to, and my favorite salmon on Tampa. I eat here 5x a week for over a year.

Food is delicious and made to order the only reason that I'm not giving it 5 ⭐ is because the wait was way too long in my opinion. I understand everything is made fresh and by order but at times it seem like the kitchen couldn't handle that many order at once, other than that food and service were great.
Expensive but healthy, flavorful and satisfying.
Looking forward to going back
Good fresh food. A bit on the pricey side.

When you want a variety of salads, this is the place.  You have tons of choices, and every one that I have had is excellent.  The green tea is really good, too.  They are a bit pricey, but it is justified for the service and quality of food.  They can get a little busy at lunch time due to their popularity, but the wait is not too long.  Highly recommended.
Okay.  It is what it is
Good choices for the healthy options. I think i found a new place for salads

my wife loves it
I will be going back everything is so fresh and delicious had the Mediterranean wrap and a chicken teriyaki bowl🥰🥰🥰 A+++ service🥇

Walked by this place after a long day at Tampa Bay Comic Con. Stopped in for a quick healthy dinner. This place has a variety of rice bowls and wraps. I had the teriyaki bowl with brown rice, cauliflower, quinoa and teriyaki sauce. I added extra vegetables and shrimp. This was delicious. I also had the strawberry, banana and honey smoothie. Yum! This place has indoor and outdoor seating. It was nice out so sat outside. There is a casual relaxed atmosphere. Service was quick and friendly. I like places with fresh and healthy options.

Love so fresh! It’s hard to stay healthy but food here is so good. There are many options to please every taste. You can also create your own in case you want to get something a bit more personalized. There are also different locations you can go to.
Listen, this So Fresh is hands down thhhhhhe best. They are courteous, friendly and professional. Deshawn and Jamar are 2 of their greatest assets.
Love this place and the food is amazing! Fast service which is great when you’re lunch time is limited.
Superior service. Super fresh food. Hip and relaxed vibe. Very child and group friendly. The fees as are so delicious! Kids meals available.

The name says it all. You can build your own bowl or choose from one theirs. Order at the counter and then choose your seat kind of place. Lots of options for vegans and vegetarians. A few tables in front of restaurant on the sidewalk. I got the Mediterranean and it was delicious. A lot of food - you might be able to split one!

I have loved this place since it opened but became a life-long fan today.  Last night I ordered the signature salad via UberEats.  I thought it came from the downtown location but I had accidentally ordered from the Soho location.  When it arrived, it was hardly edible.  The grilled chicken I had requested was fatty and brown as if the teriyaki chicken had been used.  The lettuce and cucumbers were soaking wet and left a puddle of water at the bottom of the salad.  UberEats wouldn't refund my money.  Thinking it had been from downtown, I called and we figured out it hadn't been from there.  Nonetheless, they offered to make the salad again for me free of charge, even though the salad had not come from this location.  That's customer service! Thank you, SoFresh!
Nice. Other than the checkout person being and sounding robotic it was very good. Good fresh, healthy choices.
Food is fresh!
A solid healthy food joint with lots of veggie options, with meat add-ons to build your own or take a pre-designed bowl or salad.
Clean and vibrant place. Lots of good vegan food and other options. Oh and good smoothies.

Never ordering from here here again. Excellent!

Went here for a relaxed lunch. Got the Fiji salad with chicken. Really really good with friendly staff. If it’s nice out I recommend sitting outside in the sun.

The food was fine but it was terrible value. I am on the Keto diet so I created my own salad with keto options: I got romaine lettuce, bacon, avocado, and hard boiled egg with some tzatziki dressing. I got a bowl of romaine lettuce with a few bacon bits that were clearly not fresh, probably bought pre-packaged. I got a quarter, maybe a third of an avocado. I got ONE (1!) hard boiled egg sliced up. Dressing was fine. That very measly salad cost over $15. There are plenty of alternatives in Tampa that are more cost effective.

Enjoyed my visit here after the Tampa Bay Comic Con. This is a teriyaki cauliflower quinoa and brown rice bowl with vegetables and shrimp. I had this with a smoothie. Enjoyed the relaxed atmosphere and outdoor seating in the early evening. Service was fast and friendly.
Delicious!! Highly recommend!! Reasonably priced too!

Yum... very glad I found this place..

I've been to SoFresh downtown many times because it is a healthy option close to my apartment. The first few times were great. The 3 star review is due to my last two experiences with take out. One order I placed was supposed to be a bowl and it was made as a wrap. When I brought this to the attention of the staff I was told they would remake it as a bowl but I would have to wait up to 15 minutes. I ordered take out because I did not have the time to dine-in, so something like a free drink or even just a sincere apology would have been more convenient. The more recent time I ordered a bowl that was supposed to include feta and jalapenos. It had neither. This was frustrating because I spent nearly $14 and paid extra for the feta I didn't receive. In addition, I have noticed that the take out portions are significantly smaller. I will continue to dine here, but not take out.

Tons of Vegan options, and the tofu is excellent (got the superfood bowl). First time I’ve been and it was definitely 5 stars!  Tea was very good and they have stevia for it as well! Very good food, will be back for sure.

The SF team is just as wonderful; always saying hello how are you, always engaging in friendly talks while executing transactions, truly a 5 STAR establishment.  Joey- CWs GinJoint
